{"type":"match","data":{"path":{"text":"/Users/coryflanigan/DAOS/02-Projects/goibniu/canonical/daos-engine-canonical-spec.md"},"lines":{"text":"The cascade router is composable: locally-hosted models can be added, preferred, or prioritized via the registry without changes to the routing logic. Local providers pass through all three stages; LBR treats local providers as unlimited-rate (hardware constraints are the only limit).\n"},"line_number":956,"absolute_offset":39995,"submatches":[{"match":{"text":"cascade router"},"start":4,"end":18}]}}
{"type":"match","data":{"path":{"text":"/Users/coryflanigan/DAOS/02-Projects/goibniu/canonical/daos-engine-canonical-spec.md"},"lines":{"text":"The cascade router lives in `daos_engine.bridge` — it is a transport-layer concern. Complexity classification lives in Core (CAL). This separation is load-bearing:\n"},"line_number":960,"absolute_offset":40313,"submatches":[{"match":{"text":"cascade router"},"start":4,"end":18}]}}
